mld-cli --lat -59 --lon 062 --time 2025-01-12 --plot
Run this in the terminal and it will give a density plot for the Drake Passage. An area of the ocean near the tip of South America known for being extremely turbulent. 
I chose this example because there is never a sharp density gradient change, which is why no mld value is calculated. 
This is most likely because it is such a turbulent area that there is no easily defined mixed layer depth. The density just gradually increases with depth. 